events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Jalen Duren had 22 points and a career-high 21 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons ended the Oklahoma City Thunder's five-game winning streak with a 120-104 victory on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Duren's first career 20-20 game leads the Pistons to a lopsided win over Thunder, 120-104

headlines.description: — Bennedict Mathurin scored 24 points off the bench, Jalen Smith sank a go-ahead 3-pointer late, and the Indiana Pacers won their third consecutive home game 116-110 over the Memphis Grizzlies on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bennedict Mathurin scores 24 to lead Pacers over Grizzlies 116-110

headlines.description: — Saddiq Bey dunked in Trae Young's miss with 1.1 seconds left to lift the Atlanta Hawks to a 126-125 win over the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saddiq Bey's last-second dunk gives Hawks 126-125 win over Raptors

headlines.description: — Paolo Banchero scored 26 points and the Orlando Magic beat the Phoenix Suns 113-98 on Sunday night, overcoming Devin Booker's 44-point effort two days after he had 62 in a loss at Indiana.
headlines.shortLinkText: Magic beat Suns 113-98, overcoming Devin Booker’s 44-point night

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan finished with 20 points and the Chicago Bulls snapped a two-game losing streak with a 104-96 victory over the Portland Trail Blazer on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan has 20 points and the Bulls snap 2-game skid with 104-96 win over the Blazers
